summary: I know no one cares but
body:
I know no one cares but

Here’s my dream Pokémon team

  1. Samurott

Black and White was actually the first Pokémon game my parents bought me and I don’t think I put it down for a month. And I fell in love with Oshawott from the moment I saw his sweet little freckled face and to this day Samurott is my favourite fully evolved starter

2. Mimikyu

Legit the first thing I said when I saw this sweet little ghostie was “a baby!” I frigging love Mimikyu and it’s such a sweet little thing in the games and it just wants to be loved and I will protect it with all my heart

3. Staraptor

Did I say favourite bird, because favourite bird! It’s big, awesome and I love it. I’ve had a Staraptor on every Sinnoh play through I’ve ever had and it’s never failed to make me proud

4. Leafeon

Definitely my favourite Eeveelution, such a pretty leaf baby. My Leafeon in Black and White 2 was amazing and he was my leaf son. I get why some people don’t like it as much but I love it.

5. Stoutland

Big dogo. Big friendly dogo and that episode of Sun and Moon anime made me cry.

6. Gardevoir

Leave my baby alone. She is beautiful and wonderful and loyal to the point where it’s a fault. Mystery Dungeon Gardevoir was like a gentle maternal figure to the player and still cared for the human that had cursed it. Not to mention pretty powerful

blog.name: pokegodsandmissingno
blog.title: P̵o̵K̸é̴G̸o̸D̷s̸ and Frightful Things to Come?
blog.description: There is a growing desire and expectation of humans here on Earth in making full contact with PoKéMoN who are still unknown. Back in 1995, when I saw my first UPM (Unindexed Pocket Monster), I found out very quickly that other people thought you were totally crazy if you said you saw such things. The world has changed quite a bit since then when I was a child. In fact, in late 1997, a poll taken in Kanto shows that for the first time ever, more than fifty percent of residents now believe in PokéGODS's. Since then, there have been polls that put the figure at over eighty percent or more.
